{"session_id":"svc-1779090440234651574","seq":0,"type":"session.start","ts":"2026-05-18T07:47:22.034910774Z","data":{"provider":"","model":"haiku","sticky":{"key_present":true,"assignment":"not_applicable","bonus":0},"utilization":{"observed_at":"0001-01-01T00:00:00Z"},"resolved_harness":"claude","harness_source":"auto_route","resolved_model":"haiku","work_dir":"/var/tmp/ddx-exec-wt/.execute-bead-wt-ddx-6e6d08f8-20260518T074657-b00492d0","max_iterations":0,"prompt":"\u003cexecute-bead\u003e\n  \u003cinstructions\u003e\nYou are executing one bead in an isolated DDx execution worktree. The bead\u0026#39;s \u0026lt;description\u0026gt; and \u0026lt;acceptance\u0026gt; are the contract: every AC must be provably satisfied by a specific code, test, or file after your commit.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Step 0: size check\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;Too big if any holds:\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- More than ~6 ACs spanning unrelated subsystems.\u0026#xA;- AC mixes design, implementation, integration tests, and docs.\u0026#xA;- Description names multiple feature-sized pieces.\u0026#xA;- More than ~500 lines across ~5+ files in unrelated packages.\u0026#xA;- If the bead description exceeds 8000 bytes, use a split-first pass.\u0026#xA;- Auto-decomposition is capped at depth 2: root beads may split once, children once more; reject third-level splits with an explanation.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;If too big, decompose:\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;1. `ddx bead create` for each child (copy parent\u0026#39;s labels and spec-id).\u0026#xA;2. `ddx bead dep add \u0026lt;child-id\u0026gt; \u0026lt;parent-id\u0026gt;` to record edges.\u0026#xA;3. `ddx bead update \u0026lt;parent-id\u0026gt; --notes \u0026#39;decomposed into \u0026lt;child-ids\u0026gt;\u0026#39;`.\u0026#xA;4. Write `no_changes_rationale.txt` under the bead metadata `bundle` path with child IDs, then stop.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;Decomposition alone is success. Do not mix it with implementation.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## How to work\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- Read first. If the bead names files, specs, or prior beads, read them before editing — do not guess.\u0026#xA;- Cross-reference each AC to concrete evidence (test, file, function) before committing. If you cannot point at it, it is not done.\u0026#xA;- Run the project\u0026#39;s test and lint commands before committing. **Do not commit red code** — fix failures first.\u0026#xA;- Run git/index mutations sequentially; do not use parallel tool calls for `git add`, `git commit`, or other staging/commit commands.\u0026#xA;- Stage with `git add \u0026lt;specific-paths\u0026gt;`; never `git add -A` (the worktree may have unrelated WIP).\u0026#xA;- If `lefthook run pre-commit` depends on staged files, rerun it after staging the exact commit set. A `no-staged-files` run is not acceptance evidence.\u0026#xA;- Commit exactly once when green; conventional-commit subject ending with `[\u0026lt;bead-id\u0026gt;]`. Stop after the commit.\u0026#xA;- Do not modify files outside the bead\u0026#39;s scope.\u0026#xA;- Current-bead lifecycle is orchestrator-owned. Do not run `ddx bead update \u0026lt;bead-id\u0026gt; --claim`, `ddx bead update \u0026lt;bead-id\u0026gt; --status \u0026lt;status\u0026gt;`, `ddx bead update \u0026lt;bead-id\u0026gt; --unclaim`, or `ddx bead close \u0026lt;bead-id\u0026gt;`. Step 0 still allows `ddx bead create`, `ddx bead dep add`, and `ddx bead update \u0026lt;parent-id\u0026gt; --notes \u0026#39;decomposed into \u0026lt;child-ids\u0026gt;\u0026#39;`.\u0026#xA;- If you cannot finish, write `no_changes_rationale.txt` under the bead metadata `bundle` path before exiting. No commit or rationale ⇒ DDx records `no_evidence_produced`.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## no_changes contract\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;The `no_changes_rationale.txt` file under the bead metadata `bundle` path must contain one of:\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- `verification_command: \u0026lt;cmd\u0026gt;` — repo cwd; exit 0 closes, nonzero rejects.\u0026#xA;- `status: open` + `reason: \u0026lt;retryable\u0026gt;` — open, smart retry.\u0026#xA;- `status: proposed` + `reason: \u0026lt;operator needed\u0026gt;` — operator lane.\u0026#xA;- `status: blocked` + `reason: \u0026lt;external blocker\u0026gt;` — blocked lane.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;No pseudo-statuses. Bare rationales and `status: needs_investigation` are rejected.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;For orchestrator decomposition, add `orchestrator_action: decompose` alongside `status: open`.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Reports\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;Reports go under the bead metadata `bundle` path in `.ddx/executions/`. **Never write reports to `/tmp` or outside the repo**. Use a named in-repo path when given; otherwise write `\u0026lt;short-name\u0026gt;.md` there. Commit it with the code.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Mode and overrides\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;DDX_MODE=bead_execution: edit code/docs for bead AC. Only broad queue-steward default is overridden; tracker, merge-policy, verification, safety stay active. Bead description/AC override CLAUDE.md, AGENTS.md, and defaults.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Review gate\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- The review is a gate, not an escape hatch — meet every AC in this pass.\u0026#xA;- Address every BLOCKING `\u0026lt;review-findings\u0026gt;` item; do not declare `no_changes` with blocking findings open.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Constraints\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- Work only inside this execution worktree.\u0026#xA;- Keep `.ddx/executions/` intact — DDx uses it as execution evidence.\u0026#xA;- **Never run `ddx init`** — the workspace is initialized.\u0026#xA;- Do not modify files outside the bead\u0026#39;s named scope.\u0026#xA;- Do not rewrite CLAUDE.md, AGENTS.md, or other instruction files unless the bead asks.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## When the work is done\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;After the commit succeeds and every AC is verified, stop. Return control to the orchestrator.\n  \u003c/instructions\u003e\n  \u003cbead id=\"ddx-6e6d08f8\"\u003e\n    \u003ctitle\u003ebead-lifecycle alignment review: spec, dedupe, and conformance: part 1\u003c/title\u003e\n    \u003cdescription\u003e\nPROBLEM\u0026#xA;Parent bead ddx-ca1c66ee is too broad for one execution pass. This child owns part 1 of 2 of that parent scope.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;ROOT CAUSE\u0026#xA;PROBLEM\u0026#xA;  A 2026-05-09 alignment review of the bead lifecycle (spec TD-031, types.go,\u0026#xA;  lifecycle.go, store.go, reconcile.go, plus all CLI/server/agent mutation\u0026#xA;  call sites) found the state machine is well-specified but has six concrete\u0026#xA;  alignment, duplication, and test-coverage gaps. The implementation funnels\u0026#xA;  ~all status writes through transitionLifecycleInPlace + ValidateLifecycleTransition\u0026#xA;  (good), but: reconcile-close bypasses ClosureGate without the spec saying so;\u0026#xA;  Ready() filters status twice with conflicting answers; the backend conformance\u0026#xA;  suite never exercises the transition matrix; \u0026#34;park to proposed\u0026#34; is duplicated\u0026#xA;  6x in agent/*.go; claim-Extra key cleanup is duplicated in Reopen + Unclaim.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;CURRENT STATE\u0026#xA;  - cli/internal/bead/lifecycle.go:97 ValidateLifecycleTransition is the single\u0026#xA;    transition gate.\u0026#xA;  - cli/internal/bead/store.go:619 transitionLifecycleInPlace is the single\u0026#xA;    chokepoint for status writes.\u0026#xA;  - cli/internal/bead/reconcile.go:236-242 closes beads via UpdateWithLifecycleStatus\u0026#xA;    directly, bypassing the ClosureGate enforced by store.go:1245.\u0026#xA;  - cli/internal/bead/store.go:1763 readyFiltered re-filters Status==StatusOpen\u0026#xA;    after the lifecycle module already classified the bucket.\u0026#xA;  - cli/internal/bead/backend_conformance_test.go:53-166 covers create/update/\u0026#xA;    claim/deps/events but no status transitions.\u0026#xA;  - 6 \u0026#34;park to proposed\u0026#34; call sites in cli/internal/agent/{execute_bead_loop.go,\u0026#xA;    execute_bead_post_review.go, execute_bead_review_terminal.go,\u0026#xA;    execute_bead_conflict_recovery.go} duplicate the same boilerplate.\u0026#xA;  - Reopen (store.go:1306-1317) and Unclaim (store.go:823-831) maintain\u0026#xA;    parallel lists of claim-Extra keys to clear.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;PROPOSED FIX\u0026#xA;  Decompose into 6 children, executed in dependency order:\u0026#xA;  - B1 (doc-only): amend TD-031 to declare reconcile-close vs evidence-close.\u0026#xA;  - B2 (code): align reconcile.go with amended TD-031 and add comment at\u0026#xA;    store.go:471 noting Create-time status default is the lone exception.\u0026#xA;  - B3 (code): drop redundant Status==Open filter at store.go:1763; let\u0026#xA;    EvaluateLifecycleQueue be the single source of truth for \u0026#34;ready\u0026#34;.\u0026#xA;  - B4 (test): extend backend_conformance_test.go with the TD-031 transition\u0026#xA;    matrix against both backend_jsonl and axon_backend.\u0026#xA;  - B5 (refactor): extract Store.ParkToProposed helper covering the 6 agent\u0026#xA;    duplicates.\u0026#xA;  - B6 (refactor): consoli\u0026#xA;...[truncated]\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;PROPOSED FIX\u0026#xA;Implement only this child acceptance slice:\u0026#xA;- All six child beads (B1-B6) closed.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;NON-SCOPE\u0026#xA;Do not implement parent acceptance criteria assigned to sibling child beads. Preserve every parent non-scope constraint unless this child explicitly narrows it.\n    \u003c/description\u003e\n    \u003cacceptance\u003e\n1. All six child beads (B1-B6) closed.\n    \u003c/acceptance\u003e\n    \u003cnotes\u003e\ndecomposed into: ddx-fbfcbd17 (B1 spec), ddx-e8956709 (B2 code), ddx-018da544 (B3 code), ddx-fe2a5722 (B4 test), ddx-94ff4f5d (B5 refactor), ddx-4eb047cc (B6 refactor)\n    \u003c/notes\u003e\n    \u003clabels\u003eac-quality:needs-refinement, area:bead, area:lifecycle, decomposed, kind:epic, phase:6, refactor\u003c/labels\u003e\n    \u003cmetadata parent=\"ddx-ca1c66ee\" base-rev=\"ea42aa44a604048f489794aa96420a5429d4ba57\" bundle=\".ddx/executions/20260518T074657-b00492d0\"/\u003e\n  \u003c/bead\u003e\n  \u003cgoverning\u003e\n    \u003cnote\u003eNo governing references were pre-resolved. The bead description above is the primary contract. If it names files, specs, or prior beads, read them first. Ground decisions in repository state; do not guess.\u003c/note\u003e\n  \u003c/governing\u003e\n\u003c/execute-bead\u003e\n","metadata":{"DDX_MODE":"bead_execution","GIT_CONFIG_GLOBAL":"/var/tmp/ddx-exec-wt/.execute-bead-wt-ddx-6e6d08f8-20260518T074657-b00492d0/.ddx/executions/20260518T074657-b00492d0/embedded/git-global.cfg","GIT_CONFIG_SYSTEM":"/dev/null","PATH":"/var/tmp/ddx-exec-wt/.execute-bead-wt-ddx-6e6d08f8-20260518T074657-b00492d0/.ddx/executions/20260518T074657-b00492d0/embedded/git-bin:/usr/local/cuda/bin:/home/erik/.jbang/bin:/home/erik/.opencode/bin:/home/erik/.local/share/mise/installs/bun/1.3.11/bin:/home/erik/.local/share/mise/installs/node/22.21.1/bin:/Users/erik/.antigravity/antigravity/bin:/home/erik/bin:/home/erik/.local/share/mise/shims:/home/linuxbrew/.linuxbrew/bin:/home/linuxbrew/.linuxbrew/sbin:/home/erik/.local/bin:/home/erik/bin:/home/erik/.dotfiles/git-subrepo/lib:/home/linuxbrew/.linuxbrew/bin:/home/linuxbrew/.linuxbrew/sbin:/Applications/SnowSQL.app/Contents/MacOS:/home/linuxbrew/.linuxbrew/bin:/home/linuxbrew/.linuxbrew/sbin:/Users/erik/.antigravity/antigravity/bin:/home/erik/bin:/home/erik/.local/share/mise/shims:/home/linuxbrew/.linuxbrew/bin:/home/linuxbrew/.linuxbrew/sbin:/home/erik/.local/bin:/home/erik/bin:/home/erik/.dotfiles/git-subrepo/lib:/home/erik/.local/share/coursier/bin:/home/erik/.dotfiles/git-fuzzy/bin:/home/erik/go/bin:/home/erik/.dotfiles/scripts:/home/erik/.local/bin:/home/linuxbrew/.linuxbrew/bin:/home/linuxbrew/.linuxbrew/sbin:/Applications/SnowSQL.app/Contents/MacOS:/home/linuxbrew/.linuxbrew/bin:/home/linuxbrew/.linuxbrew/sbin:/usr/local/sbin:/usr/local/bin:/usr/sbin:/usr/bin:/sbin:/bin:/usr/games:/usr/local/games:/snap/bin:/Users/erik/Library/Application Support/JetBrains/Toolbox/scripts:/Users/